              oracle.apps.saf.ta.jaudit.core.AbstractWorkspaceOrphanAnalyzer

public abstract class AbstractWorkspaceOrphanAnalyzer
extends AbstractXmlAnalyzer

The core base class for Workspace orphan Analyzers in SAF. This base class should be used by audits that need to analzye files that are not part of any project content set or the workspace content set, hence, they are orhans. This class, when coupled with the AuditWorkspaceOrphanDirectories annotation, will recursively process the list of workspace relative directories provied and call enterDocument, in the superclass. That allows the regular document level annotation filtering to take effect. If the document passes, it will then call enterFile where the implementing class can focus on the logic of the analysis for the file.

See Also:
AuditFileExtensions, AuditXmlDocumentNodeClass, AuditWorkspaceOrphanDirectories, CatalogNodeAnalyzer.java for a detailed example.
